    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks that makes sense. so the agent is basically just a middleman. what kind of stuff do they actually do to keep the money safe? like are there specific risks they're preventing exactly?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The escrow agent is indeed a middleman, but they play a crucial role in ensuring the smooth transfer of funds. They're responsible for holding the funds in a separate account, separate from the buyer's and seller's accounts, until the conditions are met. This is where the agent's expertise comes in.\n\nThe escrow agent typically monitors the transaction and verifies that all conditions are met before releasing the funds. They're also responsible for managing the risk of non-payment or default by either the buyer or seller. This can include things like ensuring the buyer has secured financing, completing any outstanding inspections or repairs, and meeting other contractual obligations.\n\nThink of the escrow agent as a \"garden watchman\" – they keep a close eye on the funds and the transaction, making sure everything stays on track and that no \"garden pests\" (like non-payment or default) can cause damage to the property or the transaction. They also handle any disputes or issues that may arise during the transaction, helping to resolve them before they escalate.\n\nIn Toronto, the escrow agent is usually a licensed professional who's experienced in handling real estate transactions. They work closely with the buyer, seller, and lender to ensure a smooth and secure transaction.",
      "source": "target",
